<div id="creative-january-marketing-ideas"></div>
<h2>Creative and meaningful January marketing ideas</h2>
<p>Here are some ways to use the awareness themes, holidays, and national days of January to connect with your audience.</p>
<ul></ul>
<h3>Share holiday recaps and roundups</h3>
<p>The holidays might be over, but don‚Äôt miss out on the opportunity to squeeze every last drop of cheer you can out of the last month! You can still make the holidays part of your January marketing by creating and publishing holiday roundup posts on your blog or on your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/january-social-media-holidays-and-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">social media</a> sites.</p>
<p>Here are some ideas:</p>
<ul>
<li>Did your catering company work a holiday party? Post pictures or recipes!</li>
<li>You can also take advantage of #tbt (Throwback Thursday) on Twitter and Instagram and post pictures from just a couple of weeks ago to share with your followers.</li>
<li>Cleaning services or home goods shops can provide post-holiday cleaning or Christmas tree disposal tips.</li>
</ul>
<p>The holidays are busy, and customers might have missed all you had going on, so this is an easy way to create content for your business while making sure they‚Äôre in the loop.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-holiday-fundraising-skip-recap.jpeg" alt="january marketing ideas - holiday recap" width="400" height="439" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-50140" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-holiday-fundraising-skip-recap.jpeg 400w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-holiday-fundraising-skip-recap-273x300.jpeg 273w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f680.png" alt="üöÄ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Free guide &gt;&gt;</strong> <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/first-page-of-google?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_10WaysFirstPageGoogle_Download">10 Tangible &amp; Free Ways to Get on the First Page of Google</a></p>
<ul></ul>
<h3>Honor Martin Luther King, Jr. Day with a day of service</h3>
<p>MLK Day, observed on the third Monday of January every year, celebrates Martin Luther King, Jr.‚Äôs birthday and commemorates his Nobel Peace Prize for¬†Civil Rights leadership. Don&#8217;t use this holiday to promote your business. Make it a day of service, celebration, and education around this civil rights legend.</p>
<ul>
<li>Many communities create a¬†<a href="https://www.nationalservice.gov/serve-your-community/mlk-day-service" target="_blank" rel="noopener">day of service</a>¬†you or your team can participate in.</li>
<li>Post quotes, photos, and facts about Martin Luther King, Jr. on social media.</li>
<li>Post stats and raise awareness about civil rights on social media.</li>
<li>Run your own day of service, whether for your community or in your company.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/january-marketing-ideas-mlk-day-of-service.jpeg" alt="january marketing ideas - martin luther king junior day of service" width="720" height="297" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-53752" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/january-marketing-ideas-mlk-day-of-service.jpeg 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/january-marketing-ideas-mlk-day-of-service-480x198.jpeg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://stockton.edu/engagement/mlk-day.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<h3>Get involved during Blood Donor Month</h3>
<p>January is National Blood Donor Month, so get involved!<em><a href="https://www.redcross.org/give-blood.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"></a></em></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.redcrossblood.org/give.html/find-drive" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Participate¬†in a local blood drive</a> or <a href="https://www.redcrossblood.org/hosting-a-blood-drive/learn-about-hosting/how-hosting-a-blood-drive-works.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">host¬†one</a> of your own.</li>
<li>Run special promotions for those in your community who donate, such as a free gift, discount code, or special deal on your products or services.</li>
<li>Raise awareness on social media and encourage your followers to give blood.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-blood-donor-month-1.png" alt="january marketing ideas - national blood donor month" width="720" height="362" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-68709" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-blood-donor-month-1.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-blood-donor-month-1-480x241.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.redcrossblood.org/give.html/find-drive" target="_blank" rel="noopener">You can find blood drives in your area here.</a></em></p>
<h3>Dish em&#8217; out on National Compliment Day</h3>
<p>Who doesn‚Äôt love a nice compliment? National Compliment Day occurs every January 24‚Äîhere are some ways to celebrate:</p>
<ul>
<li>Show another business some love on social media or by writing a review (they may even return the favor!)</li>
<li>Start a compliment train. Ask your followers to tag someone in your post and give them a compliment. The tagged person then tags another friend and gives them a compliment and so on.</li>
<li>Give your employees hand-written compliments to show them you appreciate them.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/january-marketing-ideas-compliment-day.png" alt="january marketing ideas - national compliment day" width="650" height="413" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10362" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/january-marketing-ideas-compliment-day.png 650w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/january-marketing-ideas-compliment-day-480x305.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 650px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Run fun weather-based promotions</h3>
<p>Much of the United States is covered in snow in January. Love it or hate it, you can‚Äôt stop it, so use it to your advantage! Make the snowy weather a little less gray with content, promotions, and posts celebrating the cold.</p>
<ul>
<li>Daycares can share safety tips for playing or dressing children in the snow.</li>
<li>Contractors, construction, and snow removal companies can write about winter hazards in the home‚Äîcarbon monoxide detectors, salt versus sand for ice and snow, or how to winterize drafty windows.</li>
<li>Give a snow-day discount. Anytime your city gets snow, offer a discount based on the number of inches you‚Äôve received, like 20% off for 20 inches of snow!</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/weather-based-facebook-winter-ad-example.jpg" alt="january marketing ideas - weather-based facebook ad example" width="433" height="437" class="aligncenter wp-image-11444" /></p>
<ul>
<li>You can also keep your customers up to date on the latest snow closures on your social media pages.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-winter-weather-promos.png" alt="january marketing ideas - winter weather promos" width="500" height="349" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-50146" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-winter-weather-promos.png 500w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-winter-weather-promos-480x335.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 500px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Take part in National Clean Off Your Desk Day</h3>
<p>With so many people working from home (and becoming obsessed with cleaning and organization shows), this holiday just may resonate with your audience. Here are some ways to take part:</p>
<ul>
<li>Tidy up your desk and share a before and after picture on social. Ask your audience to do the same.</li>
<li>Give organization tips and ideas</li>
<li>Run a contest or a poll. The person with the cleanest (or messiest) desk wins a prize!</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-clean-off-desk-day.png" alt="january marketing ideas - clean off your desk day" width="600" height="396" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-50145" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-clean-off-desk-day.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-clean-off-desk-day-480x317.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Share and encourage New Year&#8217;s resolutions</h3>
<p>No explanation needed for this annual favorite. Here are some ideas:</p>
<ul>
<li>Hold yourself accountable and share them with your audience. Then create content around them!</li>
<li>Fitness centers can have a weekly accountability post to create a support community.</li>
<li>Restaurants and catering services can write blog or Facebook posts with healthy recipes.</li>
<li>Daycares can blog about toy organization ideas for playrooms and toy areas.</li>
<li>Ask followers on social media what theirs are‚Äîyou could even run a poll and then write a blog post providing tips and advice for the most common resolutions.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-new-years-resolutions.png" alt="january marketing ideas - new years resolution" width="600" height="332" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-50144" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-new-years-resolutions.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-new-years-resolutions-480x266.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Check out our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/12/20/new-years-instagram-captions">135 [not overused] New Year&#8217;s Instagram caption ideas</a> post for more resolution-related ideas!</p>
<h3>Start a customer loyalty or referral program</h3>
<p>Loyal customers¬†not only bring you¬†ongoing business, but they are also more likely to refer other customers to you. Providing the best customer service is the first and foremost<a href="/blog/ws/2019/07/18/loyalty-marketing"> loyalty marketing strategy</a>, followed by intentional¬†loyalty or referral programs. And with people feeling enthusiastic and motivated for the new year, this is the perfect time to start one.</p>
<p>Here are some ideas for your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-run-customer-loyalty-programs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">customer loyalty program</a>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Create and print a simple stamp card for customers. Each purchase or service equals one stamp. After 10 stamps, customers can receive a free product, a discounted service, or a swag item.</li>
<li>Offer current customers a discount for each new customer they refer.</li>
<li>Create a tiered loyalty program so customers can move up in tiers based on their purchase history ‚Äì the higher the tier, the better discounts.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-loyalty-punch-card.png" alt="january marketing ideas - loyalty punch card" width="600" height="397" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-50142" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-loyalty-punch-card.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-loyalty-punch-card-480x318.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>As for referral programs, check out our¬†<a href="/blog/ws/2021/04/14/referral-program-ideas">14 Referral Program Ideas to Land Your Best Customers Yet</a>¬†and <a href="/blog/ws/2019/05/06/referral-marketing">these three referral marketing strategies</a>¬†to get the gears turning.¬†And make sure to promote your¬†programs on social media and in your location so customers can find out about it easily!</p>
<h3>Blame Someone Else Day</h3>
<p>This holiday changes every year. It&#8217;s the first Friday the 13th of the year, and in 2023, it falls in January! Toss the <a href="/blog/ws/2021/06/09/company-core-values">core values</a> aside today and letterrip. Don‚Äôt actually do that. But you can have fun with this one.</p>
<ul>
<li><em>&#8220;When working in a book store you learn that sometimes books are just going to fall over. Usually on their own or sometimes because of&#8230;other reasons (*cough*Ryan*cough).<br />
Happy National Blame Someone Else Day!<br />
(No books were harmed in the making of this post).&#8221;</em></li>
<li><em>&#8220;Friday the 13th: Me-ow.</em><br />
<em>National Blame Someone Else Day: You-ow&#8221;</em></li>
<li><em>&#8220;It&#8217;s okay to indulge, you can blame us!&#8221;</em></li>
</ul>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/august-marketing-ideas-national-blame-someone-else-day-compilation.png" width="720" height="442" alt="august marketing ideas‚Äînational blame someone else day social media posts" typeof="foaf:Image" /></div>
<p>Or get serious&#8230;</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/august-marketing-ideas-blame-someone-else-day-cybersecurity.png" width="450" height="474" alt="august marketing ideas‚Äîblame someone else day social media post on cybersecurity" typeof="foaf:Image" class="aligncenter" /></div>
<p>Or use it as a creative way¬†to celebrate a company milestone¬†and thank your customers. Write a customer appreciation email, blaming them for your having to bring on more employees to keep up with the demand, and for your having to move to a bigger office, and your having to choose the signature drink to serve at your party celebrating your 1000th customer&#8230;and so on.</p>
