<div id="essential-january-marketing-ideas"></div>
<h2>Essential but not-so-creative January marketing ideas</h2>
<p>These aren&#8217;t the most fun marketing ideas, but they are essential if you want running your business to stay fun, through the month and year-round.</p>
<h3>Start with a clean inbox</h3>
<p>There‚Äôs nothing less exciting than seeing the number of new <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/january-email-subject-lines/">emails</a> in your inbox when you get back from the holidays.</p>
<p>Actually, I lied because there is: It&#8217;s going through them. Did you know January 25-29 is actually Clean Out Your Inbox Week? Use it as motivation to get organized and start with a clean slate.</p>
<ul>
<li>Go through those old emails you ‚Äústarred‚Äù and never followed up on&#8230;</li>
<li>If you don‚Äôt already use folders for your emails, create some to help you keep your inbox organized.</li>
<li>Go through the settings your email platform has to offer. There are integrations, color coding, rules, and more that can make your life a whole lot easier. That half hour could translate into hours saved this year.</li>
<li>Create an ideas folder where you save marketing emails you&#8217;ve received that you like or find effective. You never know, you might just find your next great idea buried in your own inbox!</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/cliche-free-holiday-copywriting-tips-greeting-card-inbox-creative.jpeg" alt="january marketing ideas - clean inbox holiday card" width="400" height="400" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-49686" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/cliche-free-holiday-copywriting-tips-greeting-card-inbox-creative.jpeg 400w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/cliche-free-holiday-copywriting-tips-greeting-card-inbox-creative-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/cliche-free-holiday-copywriting-tips-greeting-card-inbox-creative-150x150.jpeg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
<h3>Solidify your yearly goals or marketing plan</h3>
<p>Whether you‚Äôre an agency, business owner, or freelancer, it‚Äôs important to have both personal and professional goals for the year. Take some time at the beginning of the month to make sure your goals and your marketing plan are solidified.</p>
<p>As we know, things can change quickly, but having a documented plan or a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/10/28/growth-strategy">growth strategy</a> in place can make the difference between hitting your revenue goals for the year and missing them.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f331.png" alt="üå±" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Download our¬†<a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite7StepstoGrowthStrategy.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_GrowthStrategy_Download">free, editable growth strategy template</a></strong>¬†to walk through seven simple steps for creating the right plan to grow your business.</p>
<h3>Revisit what worked last year (and what didn‚Äôt)</h3>
<p>Now that you have a full year of data available, take some time to see what worked in your marketing last year and what didn‚Äôt.</p>
<p>Here are some ideas of what to look at:</p>
<ul>
<li>What content or web pages performed best for you?</li>
<li>What resonated with your audiences on social media ‚Äì top posts, most engaging posts, etc.?</li>
<li>What <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/01/03/email-marketing-best-practices">email subject lines</a> got the best open rates?</li>
<li>What marketing strategies, campaigns, or channels drove the most leads?</li>
<li>What didn‚Äôt perform as well as you thought it would ‚Äì and how could it be improved?</li>
</ul>
<h3>Read up on the latest¬†marketing trends and predictions</h3>
<p>With the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/12/07/happy-new-year-wishes">new year</a> comes a ton of new content around what to expect in the world of marketing and business in general. Find some articles or blog posts that will get you up to speed on what the experts expect to be big this year in your own industry‚Äîand jot down some ideas or trends that you might want to try out!</p>
<h3>Announce your events for the year or coming months</h3>
<p>Market your business both online and offline by highlighting upcoming events for the year. Some upcoming holidays include President‚Äôs Day, Valentine‚Äôs Day, Mardi Gras, and St. Patrick‚Äôs Day.</p>
<p>If you have anything planned for these events, like upcoming <a href="/blog/ws/2021/01/25/valentines-day-marketing-ideas">Valentine‚Äôs Day deals</a> at your spa or a special Valentine‚Äôs menu at your restaurant, let customers know! A calendar of promotions is a great way to keep customers informed about upcoming promotions or events your business is sponsoring or hosting.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-2021-events-calendar.png" alt="january marketing ideas - upcoming events" width="600" height="335" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-50141" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-2021-events-calendar.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/january-marketing-ideas-2021-events-calendar-480x268.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Update your Google Business Profile</h3>
<p>Last, but not least, update your Google Business Profile. If you want to show up when <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/01/google-local-search-trends">local searchers</a> are trying to find businesses like yours on Google or in Google Maps, a complete and optimized Google Business profile is the place to start.</p>
<p>Take a minute to make sure your profile is claimed and then take it a step further by optimizing your listing:</p>
<ul>
<li>Make sure to respond to all reviews.</li>
<li>Add some images or a video that showcase your business.</li>
<li>Populate the Q&amp;A section of your profile with frequently asked questions.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/google-my-business-optimization-question-and-answer-section.png" alt="google business profile - Q&amp;A section" width="451" height="841" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-11608" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/google-my-business-optimization-question-and-answer-section.png 451w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/google-my-business-optimization-question-and-answer-section-161x300.png 161w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/google-my-business-optimization-question-and-answer-section-54x100.png 54w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/google-my-business-optimization-question-and-answer-section-107x200.png 107w" sizes="(max-width: 451px) 100vw, 451px" /></p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/03/google-my-business-optimization">Get more tips to optimize your Google Business Profile here</a>.</p>
<h3>Commit to growing your skill set</h3>
<p>The digital marketing world is never in a resting state. Set a goal for yourself to build on your existing marketing skills or develop new ones. Here are some great resources for doing so:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/04/13/free-local-marketing-resources">The 7 Best Local Business Marketing Resources (All Free!)</a></li>
<li><a href="/blog/ws/2021/11/03/best-facebook-ads-courses">The 8 Best Facebook Ads Courses for Every Learning Level</a></li>
<li><a href="/blog/ws/2021/12/02/best-google-ads-training-courses">The 9 Best Google Ads Training Courses for Every Level</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Hmm, looks like our next roundup will need to have 10&#8230;</p>
