					<description><![CDATA[<p>Get data and insights to help plan your 2025 marketing and stand out from the competition.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/2025-marketing-planning">10 Key Insights to Inform Your Marketing Plans in 2025</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Understanding the small business marketing landscape can be a challenge, but it‚Äôs important to know if you want to be competitive and stand out.</p>
<p>What are your competitors doing? How are they investing their marketing budgets? What are they planning for 2025?</p>
<p>LocaliQ wanted to answer all these questions and more, so we created <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/small-business-marketing-trends-report/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Small Business Marketing Trends Report for 2025</a> with data and insights from over 730 small businesses!</p>
<p>If you want to see the full report, <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/small-business-marketing-trends-report/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">jump on over to LocaliQ</a> or <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/smb-marketing-trends-report?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2025SmallBusinessMarketingTrendsReport_Download">download it here</a>. And keep reading for 10 key takeaways from the report you need to know to inform your 2025 planning.</p>
<h2>10 biggest takeaways from LocaliQ‚Äôs 2025 Small Business Marketing Trends Report</h2>
<p>We rounded up 10 fast facts from the report to help you understand the small business marketing landscape and start your 2025 planning.</p>
<h3>1. Most SMBs aren‚Äôt investing in paid search</h3>
<p>According to the report, only 40% of SMBs are investing in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/search-advertising">search advertising</a>, which means the majority of small businesses are not running ads on top search engines like Google and Bing.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-current-marketing-channels.webp" alt="marketing channels smbs are investing in according to localiq 2025 marketing trends report" width="1501" height="1594" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-86955" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-current-marketing-channels.webp 1501w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-current-marketing-channels-1280x1359.webp 1280w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-current-marketing-channels-980x1041.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-current-marketing-channels-480x510.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) and (max-width: 1280px) 1280px, (min-width: 1281px) 1501px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Plus, only 39% of SMBs are investing in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/seo">SEO</a>. This means that small businesses are largely missing out on the opportunity to capture high-intent, local searchers.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f680.png" alt="üöÄ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Free guide &gt;&gt;</strong> <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/first-page-of-google?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_10WaysFirstPageGoogle_Download">10 Tangible &amp; Free Ways to Get on the First Page of Google</a></p>
<h3>2. Less than half of SMBs are investing in social ads</h3>
<p>We were surprised to find that less than half of small businesses are investing in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/social-ads-101">social media ads</a> on platforms like Facebook, LinkedIn, and more.</p>
<p>These platforms are important because customers spend so much time on social media and are increasingly relying on them to discover new businesses. In fact, TikTok is now the <a href="https://digitalmarketinginstitute.com/blog/is-tiktok-a-search-engine" target="_blank" rel="noopener">fourth most popular search engine</a>, with <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/do-gen-z-use-tiktok-search-more-than-google-thomas-haynes-idnye/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">one in 10</a> Gen Zers more likely to use it than Google.</p>
<p>By not running ads on popular social media sites, SMBs are missing out on ways to engage and convert customers where they‚Äôre spending (a lot!) of time online.</p>
<h3>3. But SMBs running paid search are satisfied with results</h3>
<p>When it comes to how satisfied small businesses are with their marketing investments, search advertising topped the list as the tactic they are most satisfied with.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-marketing-channels-satisfaction.webp" alt="how satisfied smbs are with their marketing channel investments according to localiq 2025 marketing trends report" width="1501" height="1399" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-86956" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-marketing-channels-satisfaction.webp 1501w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-marketing-channels-satisfaction-1280x1193.webp 1280w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-marketing-channels-satisfaction-980x913.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-marketing-channels-satisfaction-480x447.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) and (max-width: 1280px) 1280px, (min-width: 1281px) 1501px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>This makes sense to us! It‚Äôs pretty easy to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-reports">measure results for search advertising</a> compared to tactics like reputation management or social media marketing, so this could definitely be a factor. But we also know that search ads are effective for small businesses at <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/11/17/website-visibility">driving website visits and conversions</a>.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>How are your Google Ads <em>really</em> performing?</strong> Find out with a free, instant audit &gt;&gt; <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader">Google Ads Performance Grader</a></p>
<h3>4. SMBs are also not taking advantage of low-cost online presence strategies</h3>
<p>Back to the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/26/marketing-channels">marketing channels</a> and tactics SMBs are investing in‚Äîwe would be remiss if we didn‚Äôt mention the lack of investment in strategies like reputation management, listings, and website chat.</p>
<p>These strategies contribute to a strong web presence‚Äî<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/03/01/business-directory-listings">listings and reputation management</a> can help you capture and draw in potential customers on search engines and map apps while chat can help you capture website leads and convert them quicker.</p>
<p>Many listings, reputation management, and <a href="https://localiq.com/products/chat/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">website chat tools</a> or strategies are also fairly low-cost, making them a strong fit for small businesses.</p>
<h3>5. Facebook is the most popular social platform SMBs are using for marketing</h3>
<p>Facebook is not only the most popular social media platform for users‚Äîit was also the most popular social platform for SMBs to use for marketing.</p>
<p>Of those businesses investing in social media marketing or social ads, nearly 80% were doing so on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/07/02/facebook-marketing-for-small-business">Facebook</a>, followed by Instagram and LinkedIn.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-social-media-channels.webp" alt="social media channels small businesses are investing in according to localiq 2025 marketing trends report" width="1501" height="1423" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-86957" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-social-media-channels.webp 1501w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-social-media-channels-1280x1213.webp 1280w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-social-media-channels-980x929.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-social-media-channels-480x455.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) and (max-width: 1280px) 1280px, (min-width: 1281px) 1501px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>6. Smaller businesses have small budgets (unsurprisingly)</h3>
<p>Okay‚Ä¶duh? But understanding the typical <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-budget/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing budget</a> for your SMB competitors is really handy. LocaliQ found that only 5% of SMBs had no budget and 38% had monthly budgets under $2,500.</p>
<p>And because the report was able to break down marketing budgets by business size, we were able to see a clear correlation between business size and budget. Which, again, isn‚Äôt necessarily a surprise, but it should be validating to small businesses who are doing so much with not a lot.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-marketing-budget-breakdown.webp" alt="monthly marketing budget breakdown for smbs according to localiq 2025 marketing trends report" width="1501" height="1749" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-86958" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-marketing-budget-breakdown.webp 1501w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-marketing-budget-breakdown-1280x1491.webp 1280w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-marketing-budget-breakdown-980x1142.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-marketing-budget-breakdown-480x559.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) and (max-width: 1280px) 1280px, (min-width: 1281px) 1501px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>This just shows the importance of adopting those <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-marketing-strategies">low-cost strategies</a> we mentioned earlier and take advantage of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/06/12/marketing-ideas">creative marketing ideas</a> to get in front of potential customers.</p>
<p>We have some you may like here:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/09/free-and-low-budget-marketing-ideas">27 Free &amp; Low-Budget Marketing Ideas for Any Business</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/15/local-marketing-ideas">42 Powerful Local Marketing Ideas That Work (+Examples!)</a></li>
<li><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/free-marketing-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">10 Free &amp; Creative Marketing Ideas for Small Businesses</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>7. They&#8217;re also less likely to have dedicated marketing support</h3>
<p>The smaller the business, the less likely they are to have staff dedicated to marketing. Which does make trying any new or additional marketing strategies a challenge‚Äîthose often take some kind of time commitment.</p>
<p>But, the report also found that many SMBs aren‚Äôt taking advantage of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/wordstream-graders">free tools</a> that could simplify some of these strategies for businesses strapped for time and resources.</p>
<h3>8. Most SMBs are already using AI</h3>
<p>Even though our team has been dabbling in AI, and our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/category/artificial-intelligence">AI-related articles</a> tend to be popular, we weren&#8217;t sure how much smaller businesses have embraced this new tech. But nearly 60% of SMBs are using AI for some part of their marketing! Most are using it to save time on activities like content creation, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-for-social-media">social media management</a>, and more.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-ai-use-for-smbs.webp" alt="percentage of small businesses using ai and how and why they use it according to localiq 2025 marketing trends report" width="1501" height="1392" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-86959" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-ai-use-for-smbs.webp 1501w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-ai-use-for-smbs-1280x1187.webp 1280w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-ai-use-for-smbs-980x909.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-ai-use-for-smbs-480x445.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) and (max-width: 1280px) 1280px, (min-width: 1281px) 1501px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>9. The economy continues to be a challenge</h3>
<p>After a tough few years for businesses‚Äîfrom the COVID-19 pandemic to record-high inflation and supply chain issues‚ÄîSMBs are still concerned about the economy. Nearly half of businesses indicated it will be their biggest challenge in 2025, with 18% noting it will be very challenging.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-biggest-smb-challenges.webp" alt="biggest challenges for small businesses in 2025 according to localiq 2025 marketing trends report" width="1501" height="1329" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-86960" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-biggest-smb-challenges.webp 1501w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-biggest-smb-challenges-1280x1133.webp 1280w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-biggest-smb-challenges-980x868.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/marketing-trends-report-2025-biggest-smb-challenges-480x425.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) and (max-width: 1280px) 1280px, (min-width: 1281px) 1501px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Plus, of those decreasing their marketing budgets in 2025, 56% noted it was due to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/small-business-challenges/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">economic conditions and uncertainty</a>.</p>
<h3>10. Getting new customers is also a top challenge</h3>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-get-more-customers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Getting new customers</a> continues to be a top challenge for small businesses, with 45% saying it will be one of their top challenges for 2025. This is something we hear time and time again‚Äî<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/lead-generation-ideas">generating leads</a> and getting new customers is hard, especially with limited budget and resources.</p>
<p>Investing in the right marketing strategy can help drive leads and capture customers, which could simplify this challenge for SMBs.</p>
<h2>Create the right marketing strategy for big results in 2025</h2>
<p>Small businesses have big <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/content-plan">plans</a> for 2025, and this round-up covers just a few of them. To see all the data and insights we gathered from over 730 SMBs, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/smb-marketing-trends-report?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2025SmallBusinessMarketingTrendsReport_Download">download the full report</a>. And <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/marketing-services?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Demo_Blog_Demo">reach out to schedule a demo</a> if you need help crafting the right marketing strategy to stand out from the competition.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs a recap of the top takeaways from The Small Business Marketing Trends Report for 2025:</p>
<ol>
<li>Most SMBs aren‚Äôt investing in paid search</li>
<li>‚Ä¶or social ads</li>
<li>But SMBs running paid search are satisfied with results</li>
<li>SMBs are also not taking advantage of low-cost online presence strategies</li>
<li>Facebook is the most popular social platform SMBs are using for marketing</li>
<li>Smaller businesses have small budgets (unsurprisingly)</li>
<li>‚Ä¶and are less likely to have dedicated marketing support</li>
<li>Most SMBs are already using AI</li>
<li>The economy continues to be a challenge</li>
<li>‚Ä¶And so does getting new customers</li>
</ol>
